ion\nand decays of the Higgs-sneutrino BRPV mixed state (assuming it is the 125 GeV\nscalar) and show that, in this case also, large deviations up to ${\\cal\nO}(100\\%)$ are expected in e.g., $p p \\to h \\to \\mu^+ \\mu^-, \\tau^+ \\tau^-$,\nwhich are sensitive to the BRPV$\\times$TRPV coupling product.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2019 18:00:01 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 29 Sep 2019 09:56:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
