asured clumpiness appears more elevated\nthan if we could resolve clumps down to single clusters. This effect is small\nin the redshift range covered by LARS, thus our results are not driven by the\nphysical resolution.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 11 Jun 2019 18:00:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-06-19"}
